<h1>Guillermo Gutiérrez Almazor</h1>
<h2>Software Repair & Restoration</h2>
<p>Software demographics show that the population is on a continuous legacifying (yes, I said that word) process.</p>

<img src="assets/demographics.png"/>

<p>As this conveniently shaped, completely unrelated graph shows, new and old companies are in a rush for producing new software faster but that only makes the problem bigger. As soon as they hit production, every software project becomes legacy, inevitably.</p>

<blockquote>Legacy software: software that's making the money</blockquote>

<p>Most of the software projects on the wild are already more than 5 years old, and often the people involved in their creation are no longer available. That entrails a huge risk for the companies that base their critical business operations on them</p>




